Install build_geometry and validate_geometry into bin/.

Upstream's apps/CMakeLists.txt defines both executables but never installs
them, so the rattler-build package was missing them and the tests block
silently failed on `test -f $PREFIX/bin/build_geometry`. Add a small
install(TARGETS ...) rule.

Literal `bin` rather than ${CMAKE_INSTALL_BINDIR} because GNUInstallDirs
isn't included until after `add_subdirectory(apps)` in v0.1.0's top-level
CMakeLists, so the variable would be empty here.

Open upstream PR adds the same install rule plus a local
`include(GNUInstallDirs)` so it can use the variable properly. Once
released, drop this patch.

--- a/apps/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/apps/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -13,5 +13,9 @@
 add_executable(validate_geometry validate_geometry.cpp)
 target_link_libraries(validate_geometry
     PRIVATE
         sqlite3
 )
+
+install(TARGETS build_geometry validate_geometry
+    RUNTIME DESTINATION bin
+)
